<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>EJS App - Static Page</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="site-header">
      <div class="container">
        <h1>Welcome to the Static HTML Page</h1>
        <p>This page is served as a normal HTML file with CSS styling.</p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main class="container">
      <section class="feature-card">
        <h2>Fast and simple</h2>
        <p>
          This example demonstrates how to serve a standard HTML page alongside
          your existing Express/EJS setup.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="feature-card">
        <h2>Styled with CSS</h2>
        <p>
          The styles are loaded from a separate <code>styles.css</code> file.
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="site-footer">
      <div class="container">
        <p>Built with Express and plain HTML/CSS.</p>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
